MAKURDI – A telecommunications mast belonging to the Nigeria Telecommunication Limited (NITEL) in Katsina-Ala, Katsina-Ala Local Government Area (LGA) of Benue state has collapsed, killing two of its workers. Daily Independent gathered that the incident which took place on Wednesday evening at the premises of the NITEL office, situated around the Takum junction, Katsina-Ala also left five other NITEL staff critically injured. Meanwhile, the Police Public Relations Officer (PPRO), Benue State Command, SP Sewuese Anene who confirmed the report said, “Two people died. Others are in the hospital.” FRSC Records 9% Reduction In Road Crashes, 26% Reduction In… Abia APC Women Threaten To Go Naked At National Secretariat We further learnt that the NITEL workers who were seven in number were on top of the mast and were in the process of dismantling it, when the mast suddenly collapsed. Also confirming the incident to newsmen in Makurdi, Alfred Atera, Chairman, Kastina-Ala LGA, who described the incident as very unfortunate explained that the incident occurred while the men were dismantling the old NITEL mast in the area. He said, “They had loosed one side of the mast when the other part collapsed. Two of them died instantly while five others were taken to the hospital.”